---
description: Feature documentation must be updated whenever feature code changes
globs:
  ["features/**/*.{ts,tsx}", "app/**/*.{ts,tsx}"]
alwaysApply: false
---

For every feature change, in the **same PR / same change set**:

1. Identify the related feature documentation in `/docs/frontend/features/`.
2. Read it before editing.
3. Update it after editing.
4. If the feature doc does not exist, create it from the template below.
5. Update `/docs/frontend/features/README.md` if you added, renamed, or changed the status of a feature.
6. Append an entry to `/docs/decisions/changelog.md`.
7. If the feature crosses Supabase, update the corresponding `/docs/supabase/*` files (see `20-supabase-mcp.mdc`).

If you find an issue but do not fix it, log it in `/docs/decisions/technical-debt.md`.

For the canonical end-to-end flow, follow `/docs/frontend/how-to-add-a-feature.md`.

## Feature doc template

Every feature doc must include:

```
# Feature Name

## Status
Implemented / Partially implemented / Not implemented

## Purpose

## User Flow

## Main Files

## Components

## Hooks

## State Management

## API / Supabase Dependencies

## Validation Rules

## UI / UX Rules

## iOS + Android Notes

## SOLID / Architecture Notes

## Performance Notes

## Known Issues

## Last Updated
```

The `Last Updated` line must include today's date and a one-line summary of the most recent change.
